# ferox-isaac-demo DDS configuration.
#
# This file is sourced by scripts/lib/env.sh (which all demo scripts source),
# so the values flow to BOTH:
#   - the Isaac Sim container (mounted cyclone XML + CYCLONEDDS_URI -e flag)
#   - the Ferox nav stack (compose passthrough via docker/.env on the Ferox side)
#
# ---- Peers are tailnet-derived, not hardcoded ----
# The <Peers> list is built at startup by scripts/lib/dds_peers.sh from the
# tailnet: this node's own `tailscale ip -4` (ALWAYS — same-host sim+nav+speech
# discovery needs it, multicast is off over the tunnel) plus every currently-
# ONLINE tailnet node (scoped to tag:ferox if that tag is in use, else all
# online peers). Because an offline host is never online, it never becomes a
# <Peer> — so the "ddsi_udp_conn_write ... failed" SPDP flood can't recur on a
# fresh (ephemeral-IP) Vast.ai instance or while a laptop peer is asleep. No
# IPs to maintain here.
#
# FEROX_DDS_INTERFACE pins the network interface (recommended over a tunnel):
#   FEROX_DDS_INTERFACE=tailscale0
# Leave it unset for single-machine sim with no Tailscale (multicast on LAN).
#
# ---- Manual override (edge cases only) ----
# Set FEROX_DDS_PEERS explicitly to bypass tailnet derivation entirely (e.g. a
# non-Tailscale VPN, or to pin a fixed list). An explicit "" means no peers
# (multicast only). If set, it MUST include this node's own tailscale IP.
#   FEROX_DDS_PEERS="100.82.193.45 100.112.212.89"
